subject: Mo BETTA
value: I liked working with you because of the advice and wisdom you have to share relative to becoming a better learner and person. When you had questions and I struggled to explain programming concepts, you stayed patient and let me try multiple times. i.e. you didn't throw your arms up and just give up, you kept pressing at it. I liked that you gave your input on the project and asked "why" i was programming certain ways. You were fully present and fully participated in all aspects, even though we loosely designated different work (i.e. me game-logic, you front-end). I did feel pressure and over-pressed when you wanted an answer for how and why I was doing certain things. Although I appreciate your patience, I felt pressed for time to explain them; I felt rushed, i.e. like you were in a hurry to get an answer from me. I struggled to understand when you were recommending we change something, or if you simply didn't understand why I was choosing a certain something. If you weren't asking purely for curiosity purposes, and actually were advocating for change, it wasn't clear which one it was (although I didn't explicitly ask either)

Your technical skills seem ok, but you seemed to have a hard time following along with stuff at times.  Of course, I know a lot of this comes from the depression and other personal issues you've been dealing with lately. In retrospect, I think maybe it would have been good if we broke out some paper or a whiteboard to diagram some stuff.
